/target
/.cargo/

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do
# not commit Cargo.lock. See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
Cargo.lock

# `fuzz/Cargo.lock` is the exception: the cargo-fuzz harness is a
# binary package per cargo's "binary → lockfile checked in" convention,
# and release-plz refuses to operate on a repo with a tracked file that
# is also gitignored. Negate the blanket `Cargo.lock` rule for it.
!fuzz/Cargo.lock
